                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>New Orleans</placeName>\n                <date>April 12. 5609</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">My dear friend,</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">Yours <date>3d.</date> inst to hand, for which<lb/> I offer many\n                thanks.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Since my last the congregation agreed to have<lb/> a temporary place\n                of worship opened. <persName>Mr. de Silva</persName><lb/> officiated on <date>1<hi\n                        rend=\"sup\">st</hi> days of <hi rend=\"underline\">Pesach</hi></date> &amp;\n                will continue so that<lb/> after all my first proposition has been adopted.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I note your remarks about <persName>Gutheim</persName>. You<lb/> are\n                in error in thinking that you had previously<lb/> answered my inquiries. Like myself\n                you have<lb/> been forgetful &amp; not sufficiently explicit several<lb/> times. I\n                have always made full allowances<lb/> for your inadvertence &amp; knowing what I\n                have<lb/> recently undergone you ought to do the same<lb/> for me. Respecting the\n                inscription I am<lb/> happy that you have given me right. With<lb/> regard to the\n                Organ, you “did the thing” just<lb/> as I wanted it, neither too much nor too\n                little.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">You will please have the <add>נר תמר</add> made to<lb/>\n                <add>?</add> into the ceiling of the ark, between<lb/> the cornice &amp; the sliding\n                doors</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Please procure a “Shophar” &amp; also<lb/> a\n                    <date><sic>Hanuca</sic></date> lamp.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Regarding the number of bells for<lb/> the sepharim, please get even\n                so 5<lb/> in all; the last two <hi rend=\"underline\">perhaps</hi> you may<lb/> as\n                well have made somewhat <hi rend=\"underline\">plainer</hi> if there<lb/> is any great\n                difference in cost; if not then<lb/> let them be like others.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3cv4cc01/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
