                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3cv4cc01/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"indent(1)\">The Hebrew Benevolent Association<lb/> at last annual meeting\n                elected me<lb/> President. They require some one<lb/> to take the lead again for a\n                while<lb/> to get things straight, to draft a<lb/> constitution &amp; by laws fit\n                for the<lb/> government of such a society, &amp; to procure<lb/> a charter. I know\n                there was great diss<lb/>atisfaction &amp; fearing that the society<lb/> might be\n                dissolved I accepted the<lb/> office which I held <del>from</del> for the two\n                first<lb/> years of its existence. The duties are severe<lb/> &amp; take up a great\n                deal of time if properly performed.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I have had two very disagreeable questions<lb/> to decide &amp; act\n                upon in my congregation, which<lb/> when we meet or I have more time I shall<lb/> be\n                happy to communicate &amp; ask your opinion<lb/> on my judgment &amp; acts in the\n                premises.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Will you be so kind as to inform me how <persName>L A<lb/> Levy\n                    Jr.</persName> who married <persName>Isabella Levy</persName> of <placeName>New\n                    York</placeName> is affected<lb/> by his <hi rend=\"underline\">legal</hi> though\n                    <hi rend=\"underline\">illegal</hi> marriage. He is a Levite<lb/> &amp; I presume\n                his marriage is not recognized by<lb/> us in calling him to “sephar” in “Schule”.\n                Yet<lb/> if we “do not go behind the curtain” he has a regular<lb/> “Ketuba”. His\n                offspring I know we regard as “momscien<add>?</add>”</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">He is a very good man but I will act according<lb/> to our law to\n                the letter. Do give my fond love to my dear little<lb/> aunt husband &amp;c when you\n                see them &amp; believe me yours sincerely</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(9)\"><persName role=\"author\">G. Kursheedt</persName>.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3cv4cc01/canvas/p3"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
